  &lt;p id="fRfrIS"&gt;With the ability to lift itself up to get over room transitions as high as 40mm, fluffy rugs, and other possible obstacles, Roborock’s new Qrevo Curv could be a sign that the stair-climbing robot vacuum is almost here. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="GwXGpx"&gt;To be clear, Roborock hasn’t said this, but based on how fast this company — and others — are innovating in this space, it feels like we’re really not that far away. SharkNinja also announced a new &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/e/24000289"&gt;robot vacuum with lifting capabilities&lt;/a&gt; this week, and the other companies are likely not far behind. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="oY34ft"&gt;Whether we need stair-climbing robovacs is a question I’m not sure I have the answer to yet.&lt;/p&gt;
